# /sensor-monitor-ds/README.md

  Monitor hardware sensors (temperature, fans, voltages, GPU, disks, CPU usage) and push values to [Bitfocus Companion](https://bitfocus.io/companion) custom variables. Use with Stream Deck buttons to display real‑time system metrics.  ## Features - Reads from **lm-sensors**, **nvidia-smi**, **AMD GPUs** (rocm-smi), **disk temperatures** (smartctl), Linux sysfs, and `/proc/stat` - **Optional libsensors** bindings for fast, low‑overhead access - **Caching** for nvidia-smi (configurable) to reduce system load - **User‑friendly TUI** to discover and configure sensors - **Daemon mode** with PID file, SIGHUP reload, and proper forking - **Alerts** (thresholds) that can set Companion variables or run commands - **Per‑sensor prefix/suffix** for variable names - **Divide by** scaling (e.g., flow sensors reporting 0.1 dL/h → dL/h)  ## Requirements  - **Operating system**: Linux (tested on CachyOS, Ubuntu, Debian, Arch) - **Python** 3.8 or higher - **lm-sensors** installed and configured (`sensors` command must work) - **Bitfocus Companion** running with HTTP API enabled (port 8000 by default) - Optional: `libsensors` (Python bindings) for faster lm-sensors access - Optional: `rocm-smi` for AMD GPU monitoring - Optional: `smartctl` (smartmontools) for disk temperatures  ## Installation  ### Recommended: pipx  [pipx](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/) installs the application in an isolated environment and makes it globally available.  ```bash sudo pacman -S python-pipx pipx ensurepath  git clone https://github.com/yourname/sensor_monitor.git cd sensor_monitor  pipx install . After installation, the following commands are available:  sensor-monitor  sensor-discovery-tui  Alternative: virtual environment (for development) bash python3 -m venv .venv source .venv/bin/activate         # bash/zsh source .venv/bin/activate.fish    # fish pip install -e . Configuration Discover sensors with the TUI bash sensor-discovery-tui The TUI shows all available sensors. You can:  Navigate with arrow keys  Press Space to toggle a sensor on/off  Edit the Companion variable name  Set a divide by factor (e.g., 10 for flow sensors)  Press s to save the configuration to sm_config.yaml  Manual configuration Edit sm_config.yaml (example):  yaml companion:   host: 192.168.1.100   # Companion IP   port: 8000   use_ssl: false  monitoring:   update_interval: 1     # seconds   max_errors: 5   variable_prefix: "sys_"   variable_suffix: "_val"  sensors:   - variable: cpu_temp     chip: "coretemp-isa-0000"     sensor: "Package id 0"     name: "CPU Package"     divide_by: 1     format: "{value:.1f}°C"     alert:       condition: "value > 85"       action: "companion_variable"       variable: "cpu_overheat"  alerts:   - condition: "value > 80"     action: "command"     command: "notify-send 'High temperature'"  enable_lmsensors: true use_libsensors: true          # requires libsensors Python package enable_nvidia: true enable_amd: false enable_disk_temp: false enable_cpu_sysfs: true enable_cpu_usage: true Create Companion custom variables The monitor cannot create variables automatically – you must create them in Companion first.  Open Companion web UI (usually http://localhost:8000)  Go to Settings → Variables → Custom Variables  Add each variable name exactly as defined in sm_config.yaml (with prefix/suffix if any)  The monitor will then update their values.  Usage All commands work in bash, zsh, and fish.  Start the monitor as a daemon bash sensor-monitor start Run in foreground (for testing) bash sensor-monitor start --foreground Check status bash sensor-monitor status Stop the daemon bash sensor-monitor stop Reload configuration without restarting bash sensor-monitor reload One‑shot test (update variables once and exit) bash sensor-monitor test View logs bash tail -f sensor_monitor.log Alerts You can define alerts that trigger when a sensor value crosses a threshold.  Action log: writes a warning to the log file (default)  Action companion_variable: sets a Companion variable (e.g., to light up a Stream Deck button)  Action command: runs an arbitrary shell command (e.g., notify-send)  Example alert in sensors list (per‑sensor) or global alerts list:  yaml alert:   condition: "value > 80"   action: "companion_variable"   variable: "high_temp"   value: "1" Troubleshooting “No sensors found” Ensure sensors command works: sensors -j  For NVIDIA GPUs: nvidia-smi must be in PATH  For AMD GPUs: install rocm-smi  For disk temps: install smartctl (smartmontools)  “Failed to set variable” in logs The Companion variable does not exist. Create it in Companion web UI.  Daemon won't start Check the log file sensor_monitor.log  Ensure no stale PID file: rm sensor_monitor.pid  TUI is blank / not showing Use a real terminal (Konsole, kitty, alacritty). Some IDEs (Cursor, VSCode) have limited terminal emulation.  Try: SENSOR_TUI_INLINE=1 sensor-discovery-tui  Uninstall bash pipx uninstall sensor_monitor License MIT
